CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 7, 1939, pg. 8, reads: "Attractive Natalie Fields - Fowler and Her Lovely Attendants - Natalie Fields became the bride of Raymond Fowler, in Bethel Church, Saturday night. This shot was snapped immediately after the preacher tied the knot.  Left to right, Priscilla Wells, Louisa Jeffries, bridesmaids; Dorothy Fields, maid of honor; the bride, Gertha McDonald, LaRue Walker, Thelma Davis.  The children are, left to right, Joan Bolden, Audrey Nelson, Marian Lee Bannister, Jeanne Ross and Grace Holley."
TitMainTitle: Wedding party from left: Priscilla Wells, Louisa Jeffries, Dorothy Fields, bride Natalie Fields Fowler, Gertha McDonald, LaRue Walker, Thelma Davis; and girls: Joan Bolden, Audrey Nelson, Marian Lee Bannister, Jeanne Ross, and Grace Holley, posed in Bethel Church
